How to Use

Check the main menu strip or the table of content.
If warnings, errors, exceptions and aborts equals 0. Then there are no ToDos for the user.
If they are not equal 0. Use the main menu navigation or the table of content to navigate, to the faulty Item.
Read the error text, and refer to the list of 'Item Types' below:

Item Types

INFO
 Content, invisible by default. Check the checkbox in the main menu at the top of the log to show items.
INCONSISTENCY
 This is not an warning or error, it indicates informations for the software supplier and can be ignored by the user
WARNING
Warnings have to be resolved by the user. Warnings will prevent your build from finishing successful
ERROR
 Errors have to be resolved by the user. Errors will prevent your build from finishing successful
EXCEPTION
Exceptions have to be resolved by the supplier, please provide your your project, RT and environment information to the supplier.
ABORT
Aborts have to be resolved by the supplier, please provide your your project, RT and environment information to the supplier.
